## Symptom

Both the library page (`/`) and the detail page (`/models/<slug>`) display `SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0` as the model's title, instead of the first real prose comment (e.g. "Multiboard-mounted holder for a cylindrical item — Multiconnect slot variant").

## Root cause

`lib/models/discover.ts:121–134`, `deriveTitle(source, stem)`:

```ts
function deriveTitle(source: string, stem: string): string {
  for (const raw of source.split(/\r?\n/)) {
    const line = raw.trim();
    if (!line) continue;
    if (line.startsWith("//")) {
      const text = line.replace(/^\/\/+\s*/, "").trim();
      if (text) return text.replace(/[—–-]\s*$/, "").trim();
    }
    break;
  }
  return stem.replaceAll("_", " ");
}
```

Walks to the first non-blank `//` line and returns it verbatim. st-871 added SPDX + Copyright headers at the top of every `.scad`:

```
// SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0
// Copyright (c) 2026 Sean O'Connor
//
// Multiboard-mounted holder for a cylindrical item — Multiconnect slot variant.
```

So the first `//` line is the SPDX identifier, and that's what gets returned. The real descriptive prose sits three lines below and is never reached.

## Fix

Skip "metadata-ish" header lines in `deriveTitle`. Minimal change, additive guard:

```ts
function deriveTitle(source: string, stem: string): string {
  for (const raw of source.split(/\r?\n/)) {
    const line = raw.trim();
    if (!line) continue;
    if (line.startsWith("//")) {
      const text = line.replace(/^\/\/+\s*/, "").trim();
      if (!text) continue;
      // Skip SPDX identifiers, copyright notices, and the blank
      // `//` separator that typically follows them. Title comes
      // from the first prose comment line.
      if (/^SPDX-[A-Za-z]+-[A-Za-z]+:/i.test(text)) continue;
      if (/^Copyright\b/i.test(text)) continue;
      return text.replace(/[—–-]\s*$/, "").trim();
    }
    break;
  }
  return stem.replaceAll("_", " ");
}
```

The `break` at the end of the `//` branch disappears — we continue through the header block until we find a real prose line or a non-comment line.

### Test

Add a case to `lib/models/discover.test.ts` (or wherever `deriveTitle` is currently exercised — might be implicit via `listModels` / `loadModel` tests):

```ts
test("deriveTitle skips SPDX + Copyright headers", () => {
  const source = [
    "// SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0",
    "// Copyright (c) 2026 Sean O'Connor",
    "//",
    "// Multiboard-mounted holder for a cylindrical item",
    "// Additional prose here.",
    "",
    "x = 1;",
  ].join("\n");
  expect(deriveTitle(source, "x")).toBe(
    "Multiboard-mounted holder for a cylindrical item",
  );
});
```

If `deriveTitle` is not currently exported, export it for the test or test via `loadModel` with a fixture.

