## Outcome: Blocked on st-kls. No code shipped.

Per bead acceptance criterion #1 ('Model compiles and renders without any local
patches to QuackWorks or BOSL2. If it won't, stop and comment on st-kls -- do
not ship a second patched build.'), this variant is not shippable at the
current pinned library SHAs.

## What was attempted

Authored `models/spraycan_holder_70mm_slot.scad` using
`QuackWorks/Modules/multiconnectSlotDesignBOSL.scad` per spec. Kept the v1
cradle (C-ring + drip cup) unchanged; replaced the snap backer with
`multiconnectGenerator(width=50, height=75, multiconnectPartType='Backer',
slotOrientation='Vertical')` — matching the library's own default preset of
2 slots x 25mm pitch on a 75mm-tall backer.

## Why it fails without patches

Two separate BOSL2 pinned-SHA (663cd7c) assertion failures inside
`multiconnectSlotDesignBOSL.scad`:

1. **On-ramp** (line 211): `cyl(..., spin=[90,0,180])` hits the same
   `is_finite(spin)` assert that blocks the snap path in st-kls.
   Workaroundable via `onRampEnabled=false` — on-ramp is purely a mounting
   lead-in. Applied this workaround and re-rendered.

2. **Dimple** (line 177): `attach(BACK, BOT, align=TOP, inside=true,
   shiftout=0.01) cylinder(...)` fails inside BOSL2
   `_find_anchor -> solve_ellipse -> unit` with 'Invalid vector'. The only
   parameter to disable this is `slotDimple=false`, but dimples are the
   position-locking retention — without them the mount slides right off.
   A working Multiconnect backer with dimples disabled is not a working
   Multiconnect backer.

Library-author-supplied default customizer values of
`multiconnectSlotDesignBOSL.scad` also fail the same way — this is a
library/BOSL2 SHA mismatch, not an authoring error on this bead.

## Findings persisted to st-kls

Expanded st-kls with:
- Specific line numbers (211 on-ramp, 177 dimple) and the BOSL2 trace.
- Confirmation that the root cause is the same pinned BOSL2 SHA that
  blocks the snap path.
- Note that any QuackWorks Multiboard backer (snap, slot, likely push-fit)
  is blocked by st-kls, not just the snap variant.
- Recommendation: prioritize pinning QuackWorks to a newer SHA or
  landing a patches/ directory over hand-patching per bead.

## Draft source (for reuse once st-kls lands)

Structurally complete, only blocked on library assertions. When st-kls
resolves, re-authoring from the spec should take minutes. Preserved here
so the design work is not lost:

```
// Multiboard-mounted holder for 70mm spray can — Multiconnect slot variant.
// Open-front C-ring cradle + drip cup + slide-on Multiconnect slot backer.
// v2 of st-ivh (snap variant). Slot backer sidesteps the QuackWorks/BOSL2
// snap incompatibility tracked in st-kls — no local library patches needed.

include <BOSL2/std.scad>
use <QuackWorks/Modules/multiconnectSlotDesignBOSL.scad>

$fn = 64;

// === User-tunable parameters ===
can_diameter       = 70;     // nominal can OD (mm)
clearance          = 0.75;   // radial slip between can and ring (mm)
ring_height        = 35;     // C-ring band height along can axis (mm)
wall               = 3;      // wall thickness, ring + cup (mm)
cup_depth          = 5;      // drip-cup depth below ring (mm)
cup_floor          = 2;      // drip-cup floor thickness (mm)
front_opening_deg  = 120;    // C-ring open-front arc angle (deg)

// Multiconnect slot backer
slot_count         = 2;      // number of vertical slots side-by-side
slot_spacing_mm    = 25;     // Multiconnect pitch (25mm standard)
backer_height      = 75;     // backer Z extent; longer = more dimple engagements
backer_thickness   = 6.5;    // library default; accommodates slot depth (~4.15mm)

// === Derived ===
ring_id    = can_diameter + 2 * clearance;      // 71.5
ring_od    = ring_id + 2 * wall;                // 77.5
backer_w   = slot_count * slot_spacing_mm;      // 50 at default

// === Layout ===
// X — horizontal across backer
// Y — depth. multiconnectGenerator produces a cuboid centered at origin
//     with slots on its +Y face (BOSL2 BACK). We keep it centered; the
//     accessory (cradle) extends into -Y so slots face away from the can.
// Z — vertical; can axis parallel to Z.
// Origin at backer geometric center.

ring_cy    = -(backer_thickness / 2 + ring_od / 2);  // ring center in -Y
cup_z0     = -backer_height / 2;                     // cup floor at bottom of backer
ring_z0    = cup_z0 + cup_depth;

// PRINT_ANCHOR_BBOX — outermost printed bbox in mm (X, Y, Z).
// X: max(backer_w=50, ring_od=77.5) = 77.5
// Y: backer_thickness(6.5) + ring_od(77.5) = 84
// Z: max(backer_height=75, cup_depth+ring_height=40) = 75
PRINT_ANCHOR_BBOX = [77.5, 84, 75];

// === Geometry ===

module multiconnect_backer() {
    // onRampEnabled=false: the library's on-ramp path calls
    // cyl(..., spin=[90,0,180]) which trips the same is_finite(spin)
    // assert in pinned BOSL2 (663cd7c) that blocks st-kls. Disabling
    // the on-ramp keeps the model patch-free; the slot still functions,
    // the accessory just slides straight onto the post without the
    // lead-in guide. Dimples for position locking remain enabled.
    multiconnectGenerator(
        width = backer_w,
        height = backer_height,
        multiconnectPartType = "Backer",
        distanceBetweenSlots = slot_spacing_mm,
        slotOrientation = "Vertical",
        onRampEnabled = false
    );
}

module cradle() {
    opening_half = front_opening_deg / 2;
    difference() {
        union() {
            translate([0, ring_cy, ring_z0])
                cylinder(h = ring_height, d = ring_od);
            translate([0, ring_cy, cup_z0])
                cylinder(h = cup_depth, d = ring_od);
        }
        translate([0, ring_cy, ring_z0 - 0.1])
            cylinder(h = ring_height + 0.2, d = ring_id);
        translate([0, ring_cy, cup_z0 + cup_floor])
            cylinder(h = cup_depth - cup_floor + 0.1, d = ring_id);
        // Open-front wedge faces -Y (away from the backer).
        translate([0, ring_cy, ring_z0 - 0.1])
            linear_extrude(height = ring_height + 0.2)
                polygon(concat(
                    [[0, 0]],
                    [for (a = [-90 - opening_half : 2 : -90 + opening_half])
                        [(ring_od + 10) * cos(a), (ring_od + 10) * sin(a)]]
                ));
    }
}

// Sibling expressions at root: multiconnectGenerator uses BOSL2 diff()
// tags internally and breaks when nested inside an outer union().
multiconnect_backer();
cradle();
```

## Acceptance criteria: none met, by design

1. Compile without patches -- FAILED (library asserts at pinned SHA).
2. PRINT_ANCHOR_BBOX declared -- YES (77.5, 84, 75), unverified.
3. Renders show slot geometry -- NOT PRODUCED.
4. STL watertight -- NOT PRODUCED.
5. Deviations justified -- YES, here.
